1.0 of 5 bubbles
Typical Bait and Switch
May 2016 ‚Ä¢ Couples
For May 20, 2016, my wife and I were booked on one the Paradise Luxury Cruises through our travel agent in Vietnam. We drove 4 hours from Hanoi to Ha Long and found the terminal for Paradise Luxury Cruise. When we tried to check in, the personnel had no record of our reservation! After we showed them our voucher and our guide talked to them, they told us to go to another counter which did not belong to Paradise Cruises. We told them we will not go on another cruise, but only the one we paid for, an "Operations Manager" by the name of Mr. Jade Kamal, came by. He did have our name on this alternate cruise roster because according to him the Luxury Boat we had paid for had developed "mechanical problems". They had sent out an e-mail to our travel agent just as we were arriving to board the boat. This manager had no other way to accommodate us and did not try to explain what was the level of the alternate boat and how they would compensate us for the lower level of the cruise.
At that point we decided to abort our trip and we drove three hours back to Hanoi. Our travel agent provided us hotel room in Hanoi and offered us dinner that night. We do understand that Paradise Cruises has given full refund back to our travel agent, but we do not know if they have done anything else for them to compensate for the trouble they caused us.
By the way, another overnight boat caught fire on May 6, 2016 and the people on board had to be evacuated. It appears that Ha Long Bay has become a huge tourist
operation and the natural beauty that is the object of this type of trip has been replaced by the party cruises and spa treatments on board. There are just too many boats and people on this site now.
Written June 3, 2016
